name: politico
text: RT @burgessev: Coronavirus wreaking havoc on Senate GOP now. Second Judiciary Committee member, Thom Tillis of North Carolina, has tested positive.

name: politico
text: RT @RyanLizza: The President of the United States, who is 74 and was just medevacked to the hospital, is “having some trouble breathing,” and we are learning about it from an anonymous source. https://t.co/DP9kkso0ZG

name: politico
text: RT @AndrewDesiderio: BREAKING: Sen. Thom Tillis (R-N.C.) tests positive for Covid-19. Says he has no symptoms. https://t.co/jM3vwqvze9

name: politico
text: President Trump’s #Covid diagnosis set off a scramble to contact and trace thousands of people across at least half a dozen states, a public health crisis fueled by the White House’s disregard for the simplest pandemic containment tools https://t.co/AFez3a6yO2

name: politico
text:
